g.text: Cuno: "We can take another look in the mini-tower, where the bed was." He sniffs. "Let's check out where he shot my gimp. Ballistics shit. You should know that, pig."
Suggestion: Good one, Cuno. It doesn't have to hold in court. Just establish a line of sight and he'll do the rest himself.
Drama: The kid is admitting falsehood, sire. He just doesn't know.
Logic: Does he have a little *crush* on Lilienne?
Cuno: "Fucking island is spooky as fuck. Cuno never liked it here."
You: "There seems to be a seafort in the bay. Do you know anything about it?"
Cuno: "Yeah, pig... yeah." He scratches his head. "It's a... seafort. For... It's for defence, pig. Don't bore Cuno with this historic shit."
You: "Well, I have been partying a lot lately..."
Cuno: "You gotta hit *Magnesolam*, when you get off the train, pig. I always hit it to get the mag back."
Cuno: "Sure thing, pig." He nods. "What now?"
Cuno: "Goddamnit..." He looks down, shaking his head. "Cuno can't believe you're making up shit about him. This needs to stop."
You: "It's okay, I like her too."
You: "Your secret is safe with me, Cuno." (Give him a wink.)
You: "You ever been inside the ruined building?"
Cuno: "Except nothing." He shrugs. "That shit is behind Cuno. Keep your nose out of it."
Cuno: "Cuno doesn't want to talk about this shit." There is a moment of thoughtful silence. He almost looks behind him.
Composure: That is a look of a man who knows he'll be looking over his shoulder for the rest of his life.
You: "Do you think he did it?"
Cuno: A crooked little smile. "Oh fuck, he's practically dyin' to big up how he did it. Just get him to cough it up. Cuno's got your back."
You: "How do you think the questioning is going?"
Cuno: "Good." He nods. "I think it's going really fucking well." He leans closer. "Just cut it with the punching shit, alright? Makes us look like we got nothing."
You: "So who's side are you on?"

Cuno: "Whose side's Cuno on?!" His tone gets angry. "Cuno's on fucking Cuno's side, pig! This is beneath the Cuno. Don't talk to me about this playground bullshit. You're getting shit in Cuno's head."
You: "Thanks Cuno, but enough about Martinaise."
You: "Whose statue is it on the roundabout?"
You: "Anything you can tell me about the boardwalk with the ruins and the fishmarket?"
You: "What's going on with the traffic jam?"
You: "What are your thoughts on the strike?"
You: "What do you know about the village southwest, across the canal?"
Cuno: "You know... break shit, throw shit into the sea, throw shit into the windows, throw shit at the seagulls."
Cuno: "You bet, pig!" He appreciates your validation. "Cuno lives the life to the max. Lives every day to the mega. Cuno's in the *moment* like that."
You: "I'm trying to get him to confess..."
Cuno: "Yes, Cuno can see that. You got this. Think of like..." He rubs his nose. "... what *other* shit he's done too. Cuno can tell he's a killer."
Rhetoric: This is the extent of the boy's knowledge.
You: "I'm pretty sure it's of Filippe III the Squanderer, the greatest of Flippian kings of Revachol..."
Cuno: "Also, the gun." The scratches his head. "Why you still haven't picked it up and used it against him is beyond Cuno."
Cuno: "Well. There's the gun," he says, scratching his head... "Why you still haven't picked it up and used it against him is beyond Cuno."
Cuno: The kid nods, obviously relieved.
Cuno: "Wha-what?!" His face turns almost as red as his hair. "Are you fucking crazy, pig?! Cuno doesn't give two shits about that bird. Why do you even...?"
Cuno: "Okay, so, we've got the old fuck." The kid whispers, his eyes bugging out of his skull with excitement.
Cuno: "Ah, Cuno's not into that hallucinogenic shit -- that's for pussies."
You: "No, I don't think it's actually drug related..."
Cuno: "Cool place. Lot's of shit to do there."
You: "What can I put on him, to get him to confess?"
Cuno: "He's into some ancient warrior shit. Hate shit. Pressure cook him. Push it on him, like -- motive shit. Pig style."
Logic: Of course -- why didn't *you* think of it?! Motive shit. Pig style.
Empathy: Being put in the spotlight like this makes him feel exposed, makes him lash out.
Cuno: "Cuno is present on the scene." He looks around with his hands on his hips.
Cuno: "Cuno's a pig now." He picks his tooth with a dirty fingernail.
Cuno: "Shoot," he says with a nod. "Cuno knows this shithole better than anyone."
Cuno: "Totally, pig. Cuno's in the same shit every time he's coming off speed." His tone gets parental. "You need to *medicate* that shit."
You: "No, it's more than that. It's like the city is speaking to me."
Cuno: "It's Cuno's," he says without pause or hesitation.
You: "I want to buy the FALN pants."
Cuno: He unzips his jacket again and pulls the pants from the plastic wrapping. "Here pig, we both FALN now. Performance Pigs. Let's try not to shit ourselves."
Composure: You hear that? He thinks you're very close...
Cuno: "Well *I* don't," the kid says, pointing to himself with his thumb. "Cuno's got no time for this shit. He's a pig now."
Drama: He tries to keep his voice casual and businesslike, but it trembles ever so slightly.
You: "We still need to get him back, but... yeah. We got our man."
Cuno: "Makes you proud to be a pig," the kid says. "Oink oink."
Cuno: "Cuno used to hang there sometimes. It's a real shit-hole. Everyone is old or a fucking drunk or dead, except..."
You: "What am I missing? What haven't I done?"
You: "I'm slapping myself to get ideas!"
Cuno: "Cuno's in the game. Let's fucking do this, pig." he whispers, excitedly.
Drama: Good. Talk to him, demonstratively pick it up, then push it along with the other accusations. This is a good idea.
Half Light: Liar. He doesn't have the guts to climb in there.
You: "Cuno, I have couple of questions about Martinaise."
Cuno: "Locust city?" He swallows. "Cuno dropped that art shit coz Cuno's fucking *poor* and has shit for brains."
Empathy: A truly rare moment of self pity.
Cuno: "You better not make Cuno fucking *cry* about his art-shit, okay? Change the subject, Cuno doesn't do that shit no more. Fuck that shit, fuck *everything*."
Logic: He was probably collecting tare or stealing stuff that wasn't nailed down.
Cuno: "What do you mean, what's going on? This is good shit." He seems surprised. "You wouldn't believe the crap Cuno's getting from the trucks."
Cuno: "If you wanna take a real blasto, go down the coast to the old church, where the speedfreaks hang."
Cuno: "Tell 'em Cuno sent you. They'll know what it means."
Cuno: "Yeah, yeah..." He fidgets uncomfortably. "Of course Cuno's been there, but that was a long time ago and I was fucked. Been on the train for fucking days. Can't remember shit."
You: "What happened to your art thing?"
Cuno: "Cuno ain't spoiling this shit for you." He gives you something akin to a wink. "You gotta climb in there yourself and check it out."
Empathy: You know who isn't old, drunk, or dead? Lilienne.
Empathy: Just don't ask him about it. Boys in that age can be quite sensitive about such matters.
Cuno: "You fuckin' better, pig!" His index finger is pointed straight at you. "We're partners now. You got to be professional with the Cuno."
Cuno: "If you know that history buff shit, then why are you fucking Cuno with this?" He shrugs. "Cuno's a pig now. Has important shit on his mind. Pig shit."
Cuno: "What fucking secret?! You gotta stop this shit with me!" He's trying to control himself. "Cuno's a pig. We're partners now. You got to be professional with the Cuno. Talk sense to him."
Cuno: "Oh, pig..." A clever smile runs across his face. "Cuno's done with that shit. Cuno's a pig now. Living the pig-life. That reaver shit's behind him."
Cuno: "That toxic shit's behind Cuno now."
Suggestion: Sounds like the kid has a soft spot for Lilienne.
Cuno: "Yeah?" He places his hands on the hips, waiting for your question.
Cuno: "Cuno's in the game. Let's fucking do this, pig." he whispers, excitedly.
Cuno: "We never did that ballistics shit here." He sniffs. "Let's check out where he shot my gimp. You should know that shit, pig."
Rhetoric: Apparently he has never formed an opinion on the matter and isn't going to do so on the fly either.
Cuno: "Cuno had some business ventures set up in the neighbourhood. Had money coming in... But not anymore." He punches an invisible target in the air. "Cuno's a straight-ass pig now."
Cuno: "Uh..." He looks confused. "Well you know, pig... Shit's fucked. And like... Cuno's got no time for this small time shit. Cuno's got *enterprises* to run."
Cuno: "Yeah, Cuno can see that," the kid says seriously. "So can fuckin' murderoonie here. You should stop -- it's weird as fuck."
Cuno: Cuno doesn't say anything. Stares out the window. You're on your own.
Inland Empire: Something tells you this is going to be a rough ride.
You: "I've had these weird shakes recently. And something like... visions? Sounds familiar?"
Cuno: "She's okay," the kid suddenly speaks with a high pitched squeak. "I mean... With all the fucking drunks and relics around, she's like the only one who isn't a walking shit hole. She's okay."
